narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I absolutely would recommend it. It is a relatively easy language, very structured, and very well taught.
This is the first language class I genuinely looked forward to each day. I strongly encourage anyone considering Hebrew 110 to take it with Prof. Dvoretzky.

Hebrew 110 is a great class if you want to learn Hebrew! Ayala is a wonderful teacher to learn from. It takes a lot of consistent work, but you will surprise yourself at the end of the semester by how much you have learnt.
It is a hard language and the class has a lot of work, but I learned an immense amount.
